\n|<small>Body only, built 1894. Running on under-frames from LMS 33007 BGZ (built 1940). Operational.</small>\n|L&YR lined light over dark brown.\n|~\n|-\n|2856\n|GNR Composite Lavatory Brake\n|<small>Built 1898. On display.</small>\n|GNR varnished teak.\n|[[File:GNR 2856 Carriage (1569668407).jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|1661\n|NER Clerestory Saloon\n|<small>Built 1904. Operational.</small>\n|LNER varnished teak.\n|[[File:NER Inspection Saloon No.1661 (LNER No.21661) (6966750690).jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|135\n|LYR Director's Saloon\n|<small>Built 1908. On display.</small>\n|L&YR lined light over dark brown.\n|[[File:Lancashire & Yorkshire Railway Saloon \u2018No2\u2019 (20524424515).jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|1474\n|LYR Hughes taper-end Brake\n|<small>Built 1910. Operational.</small>\n|L&YR lined light over dark brown..\n|[[File:LYR 1474 Hughes taper-end Brake Third (L&YR) built 1910.jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|427\n|Metropolitan 'Dreadnought' Brake\n|<small>Built 1910. Operational.</small>\n|London Transport brown.\n|[[File:160731.021. Oakworth, KWVR.jpg|175px|.]]\n|-\n|47\n|LYR Blackpool Club Car\n|<small>Built 1912. Running on BR 46145 Mk1 Second (built 1954) under-frames. Operational.</small>\n|L&YR lined black and brown.\n|[[File:Rth LYR 47 KWVR Oxenhope 30.06.13.jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|465\n|Metropolitan 'Dreadnought' 9-compartment third\n|<small>Built 1919. Operational.</small>\n|London Transport brown.\n|[[File:Metropolitan Railway Dreadnought Coach (17190013338).jpg|175px]]\n|-\n|509\n|Metropolitan 'Dreadnought' 7-compartment First\n|<small>Built 1923. Operational.</small>\n|Metropolitan Railway lined varnished teak.\n|[[File:Dreadnoughts at North Weald July 2013.JPG|175px]]\n|-\n|3554\n|SR 'Matchboard' Continental Brake third\n|<small>Built 1924. Operational.</small>\n|BR carmine and cream.\n|[[File:SR Matchboard Continental Brake third 3554 at Keighley.JPG|175px]]\n|-\n|8761\n|LMS CK\n|<small>Built 1924 (later World War II Ambulance Car). Awaiting restoration.</small>\n|\n|~\n|-\n|84\n|Pullman L